@{
    ViewBag.Title = "About PFT - LMS";
}
@Styles.Render("~/Content/css")
<div class="container mt-5">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-md-10">
            <div class="text-center mb-4">
                <h1 class="display-6 font-weight-bold text-primary">About The Physical Fitness Test LMS App</h1>
                <p class="lead text-muted">With Banking System Integration</p>
            </div>

            <div class="card about-card mb-5">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <p>The Physical Fitness Test LMS App with Banking System is a forward-thinking, cloud-based platform that reshapes how fitness assessments are conducted and taught in Physical Education (PE). Designed for the Philippine education system and in line with international health and education standards, the app meets the growing need for innovative tools in blended learning environments.</p>

                    <h2 class="text-dark font-weight-bold mt-4 mb-3">National and International Alignment</h2>
                    <p>In the Philippines, the Department of Education (DepEd) mandates physical fitness testing as an essential part of the PE curriculum. These tests assess critical components of physical fitness such as cardiovascular endurance, strength, flexibility, and body composition. This mandate is supported by national laws like RA 10588, the National Athletes, Coaches, and Trainers Benefits and Incentives Act, which promotes athletic excellence, and RA 5708, the School Physical Education and Sports Development Act of 1969, which requires physical fitness tests to monitor students’ health and development.</p>

                    <p>Internationally, organizations such as the World Health Organization (WHO) and the International Council of Sport Science and Physical Education (ICSSPE) provide inclusive and scalable physical fitness testing guidelines. The app also aligns with global rights-based frameworks like the Convention on the Rights of the Child (CRC), which emphasizes the right of every child to a healthy life, and national fitness programs such as the U.S. Presidential Youth Fitness Program.</p>

                    <h2 class="text-dark font-weight-bold mt-4 mb-3">E-Learning Management System (LMS) Integration in Physical Fitness Testing</h2>
                    <p>The integration of an LMS in the app enables flexible, accessible, and engaging fitness testing in a blended learning environment. Here are some of the main advantages:</p>
                    <ul class="list-group list-group-flush mb-4">
                        <li class="list-group-item">Accessibility and Flexibility: Students can access fitness modules and take assessments from any location, ensuring continuity even during remote learning.</li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">Data-Driven Personalization: The LMS collects data to track student performance, enabling teachers to provide customized fitness plans and assessments.</li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">Engagement Through Gamification: The app features gamified elements, such as challenges and interactive videos, making fitness testing enjoyable and motivating students to improve.</li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">Cost-Effectiveness: LMS platforms reduce the need for physical resources by using digital tools for testing, which lowers costs.</li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">Standardization Across Regions: The app’s protocols ensure that fitness assessments are consistent across various schools, regions, or countries.</li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">Global Collaboration: Through the cloud-based LMS, students worldwide can participate in shared challenges, promoting cross-cultural learning and physical activity.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h2 class="text-dark font-weight-bold mt-4 mb-3">Key Features of the App</h2>
                    <ul class="list-group list-group-flush mb-4">
                        <li class="list-group-item">Cloud-Based LMS Accessibility: The cloud platform allows 24/7 access to fitness tools, lessons, and tracking, ensuring students and teachers stay connected across different learning settings.</li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">Fitness Tracking and Personalization: Wearables and manual input enable real-time monitoring of student fitness progress, allowing teachers to create tailored fitness programs.</li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">Banking System Integration: Students earn virtual points for meeting fitness milestones, which can be redeemed for rewards. This not only motivates students but also teaches financial literacy.</li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">Real-Time Data Analytics: Teachers receive up-to-date analytics on student performance, helping to create data-driven lesson plans and provide immediate feedback.</li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">Blended Learning Support: The app is compatible with both in-person and online instruction, ensuring seamless transitions between physical and digital PE classes.</li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">Interactive and Gamified Features: Fitness challenges, leaderboards, and digital badges keep students motivated and actively engaged in their fitness journey.</li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">Financial Literacy Through Banking: The banking system helps students learn the value of effort and savings, adding an educational dimension to physical activity.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h2 class="text-dark font-weight-bold mt-4 mb-3">Advantages for Teachers and Students</h2>
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-md-6">
                            <h4>For Teachers:</h4>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Time-saving through automated tracking and grading.</li>
                                <li>Real-time data for personalized instruction.</li>
                                <li>Reduced administrative burden and increased focus on student outcomes.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-6">
                            <h4>For Students:</h4>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Increased engagement via gamified elements and the banking system.</li>
                                <li>Flexibility to learn at their own pace in a blended environment.</li>
                                <li>Holistic development, combining physical fitness with financial literacy skills.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <h2 class="text-dark font-weight-bold mt-4 mb-3">Global Scalability</h2>
                    <p>The app is scalable and adaptable for use in different educational systems worldwide. With cloud technology, it can be implemented in both urban and rural settings, providing consistent quality physical education. It is built to align with global fitness standards, ensuring that students everywhere have access to modern, data-driven physical fitness tests.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>